{"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectProtocol\/takeRef()"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glibobject\/objectprotocol\/takeref()"]}],"metadata":{"extendedModule":"GLibObject","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"takeRef","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:10GLibObject0B3RefV","text":"ObjectRef","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}],"modules":[{"name":"GLibObject"}],"role":"symbol","roleHeading":"Instance Method","title":"takeRef()","externalID":"s:10GLibObject0B8ProtocolPAAE7takeRefAA0bE0VSgyF","symbolKind":"method"},"sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectProtocol"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"code":"object","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is floating, sink it.  Otherwise, do nothing."}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"takeRef","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"() -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectRef","text":"ObjectRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:10GLibObject0B3RefV"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","level":2,"text":"Discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"In other words, this function will convert a floating reference (if","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"present) into a full reference."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Typically you want to use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_ref_sink()"},{"text":" in order to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"automatically do the correct thing with respect to floating or","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"non-floating references, but there is one specific scenario where","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"this function is helpful."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The situation where this function is helpful is when creating an API"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that allows the user to provide a callback function that returns a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"GObject. We certainly want to allow the user the flexibility to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"return a non-floating reference from this callback (for the case","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"where the object that is being returned already exists)."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"At the same time, the API style of some popular GObject-based"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"libraries (such as Gtk) make it likely that for newly-created GObject"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"instances, the user can be saved some typing if they are allowed to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"return a floating reference."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Using this function on the return value of the user’s callback allows"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the user to do whichever is more convenient for them. The caller will","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"always receives exactly one full reference to the value: either the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"one that was returned in the first place, or a floating reference","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that has been converted to a full reference.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This function has an odd interaction when combined with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_ref_sink()"},{"type":"text","text":" running at the same time in another thread on"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the same "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Object","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" instance. If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_ref_sink()"},{"text":" runs first then","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the result will be that the floating reference is converted to a hard"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"reference. If ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_object_take_ref()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" runs first then the result will be","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"that the floating reference is converted to a hard reference and an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"additional reference on top of that one is added. It is best to avoid"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"this situation."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"references":{"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/Object":{"url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/object","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/Object","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Object","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","title":"Object","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Object","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The base object type."}],"role":"symbol"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject","abstract":[],"role":"collection","kind":"symbol","title":"GLibObject","type":"topic"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/ObjectRef":{"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectRef","abstract":[{"text":"The base object type.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"ObjectRef","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/objectref","title":"ObjectRef","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ObjectRef","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/ObjectProtocol":{"url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/objectprotocol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectProtocol","title":"ObjectProtocol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ObjectProtocol"}],"abstract":[{"text":"The base object type.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ObjectProtocol","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/ObjectProtocol/takeRef()":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"takeRef","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ObjectRef","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:10GLibObject0B3RefV"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/objectprotocol\/takeref()","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/ObjectProtocol\/takeRef()","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"code":"object","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is floating, sink it.  Otherwise, do nothing."}],"title":"takeRef()"}}}